    "name": "Phasmadaemon",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Among the most powerful members of daemonkind, the phasmadaemons personify death by fright, and conjure powers of illusion so terrifying that they steal the life from their victims. A phasmadaemon is 25 feet long from snout to tail, but can compress itself into surprisingly small areas thanks to its strange, elastic anatomy. It weighs half a ton."
        }
    ],
    "html": "<i>This serpentine monstrosity has the long snout of a crocodile, ram\u2019s horns, and mantis claws projecting from its sinuous body.</i>",
